== History == Originally a {{ill|Shabō|ja|社坊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shabō|qq=}} (a temple associated with a Shinto shrine) of [[:en:Suwa-taisha|Suwa-taisha]], Kannoni-in served as a {{ill|Prayer Temple|ja|祈願所|1=Kigan-sho|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prayer Temple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kigan-sho|qq=}} for the [[:en:Suwa clan|Suwa clan]] during the medieval period. The temple is situated on a hill overlooking [[:en:Lake Suwa|Lake Suwa]], providing a scenic view of the surrounding area.
The temple was revived during the early Edo period under the patronage of {{ill|Suwa Tadatane|ja|諏訪忠恒|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Tadatane|qq=}}, the lord of the [[:en:Suwa Domain|Suwa Domain]]. The current main hall was rebuilt in 1715 (Shōtoku 5) by {{ill|Suwa Tadatora|ja|諏訪忠虎|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suwa Tadatora|qq=}}.
